          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt Promotion Across Environments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A prompt version that works correctly in development may silently behave differently under production traffic patterns. Environment-gated promotion forces each version to prove itself at increasing levels of trust before reaching all users."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Promote the artifact, not the edit. Each environment pins an immutable version by semver tag \u2014 it never picks up changes via a mutable reference like 'latest'."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This sub-subtopic covers the four-environment promotion model (dev \u2192 staging \u2192 canary \u2192 production), the gates that guard each transition, and the tooling to automate promotion and automatic rollback."
          }
        ]
      },
