      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Staging and canary run against the same artifact registry. The deployment config is the only thing that changes \u2014 not the artifact."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deployment Config per Environment"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each environment has its own versioned config file. The config is committed to Git and deployed by the CD pipeline \u2014 no manual edits on servers."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# deploy/config/dev.yaml\nprompts:\n  triage:\n    name: triage-v2\n    version: \"1.3.0-dev.4\"\n    sha256: \"c7a3e1...\"\n  summariser:\n    name: summariser\n    version: \"2.1.0-dev.1\"\n    sha256: \"d2b9f4...\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# deploy/config/staging.yaml\nprompts:\n  triage:\n    name: triage-v2\n    version: \"1.3.0-rc.1\"\n    sha256: \"a1b2c3...\"\n  summariser:\n    name: summariser\n    version: \"2.0.0\"\n    sha256: \"f12a3d...\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# deploy/config/production.yaml\nprompts:\n  triage:\n    name: triage-v2\n    version: \"1.2.0\"\n    sha256: \"b9c4f1...\"\n  summariser:\n    name: summariser\n    version: \"2.0.0\"\n    sha256: \"f12a3d...\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The canary environment uses the same file as production but with an override for the prompts under test:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# deploy/config/canary.yaml\n# Inherits production.yaml; overrides only the prompt under canary test\nprompts:\n  triage:\n    name: triage-v2\n    version: \"1.3.0\"\n    sha256: \"e8d5a2...\"\n    canary_weight: 5          # percentage of requests routed to this version\n  summariser:\n    name: summariser\n    version: \"2.0.0\"\n    sha256: \"f12a3d...\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Promotion Gate: Staging to Canary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The promotion script runs the full eval suite against the staging deployment, checks latency, and only opens a PR to update the canary config if all gates pass:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scripts/promote_to_canary.py\nimport subprocess, sys, json, yaml, anthropic\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nMIN_EVAL_SCORE = 0.92\nMAX_P99_MS = 3000\nEVAL_SUITE = Path(\"evals/triage-v2-full.json\")\n\ndef run_evals(version: str, artifact_path: str) -> dict:\n    cases = json.loads(EVAL_SUITE.read_text())\n    client = anthropic.Anthropic()\n    prompt_cfg = yaml.safe_load(Path(f\"{artifact_path}/prompt.yaml\").read_text())\n\n    correct, latencies = 0, []\n    for case in cases:\n        import time\n        msg = prompt_cfg[\"user_template\"]\n        for k, v in case[\"inputs\"].items():\n            msg = msg.replace(\"{{ \" + k + \" }}\", v)\n\n        t0 = time.monotonic()\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model=prompt_cfg[\"model\"],\n            max_tokens=prompt_cfg[\"max_tokens\"],\n            temperature=0.0,\n            system=prompt_cfg[\"system\"],\n            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": msg}],\n        )\n        latencies.append((time.monotonic() - t0) * 1000)\n        try:\n            result = json.loads(response.content[0].text)\n            if result.get(\"category\") == case[\"expected_category\"]:\n                correct += 1\n        except (json.JSONDecodeError, KeyError):\n            pass\n\n    latencies.sort()\n    p99 = latencies[int(len(latencies) * 0.99)]\n    return {\n        \"score\": correct / len(cases),\n        \"p99_ms\": p99,\n        \"n\": len(cases),\n    }\n\ndef promote(prompt_name: str, version: str):\n    artifact_path = f\"prompts/{prompt_name}/{version}\"\n    results = run_evals(version, artifact_path)\n    print(f\"Eval score: {results['score']:.3f} (need {MIN_EVAL_SCORE})\")\n    print(f\"p99 latency: {results['p99_ms']:.0f}ms (need < {MAX_P99_MS}ms)\")\n\n    if results[\"score\"] < MIN_EVAL_SCORE:\n        print(f\"FAIL: eval score {results['score']:.3f} below threshold\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    if results[\"p99_ms\"] > MAX_P99_MS:\n        print(f\"FAIL: p99 latency {results['p99_ms']:.0f}ms above threshold\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    print(\"Gates passed. Opening PR to promote to canary...\")\n    # In practice: update deploy/config/canary.yaml and open a PR via GitHub API\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    promote(sys.argv[1], sys.argv[2])\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Canary Traffic Splitting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The canary environment runs two versions simultaneously. The application layer routes a fixed percentage of requests to the candidate version based on the deployment config:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/prompt_router.py\nimport random, yaml\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom .prompt_loader import load_prompt\n\n_configs = {\n    \"canary\": yaml.safe_load(Path(\"deploy/config/canary.yaml\").read_text()),\n    \"production\": yaml.safe_load(Path(\"deploy/config/production.yaml\").read_text()),\n}\n\ndef get_prompt_for_request(prompt_key: str, env: str = \"production\") -> tuple[dict, str]:\n    cfg = _configs[env][\"prompts\"][prompt_key]\n\n    if env == \"canary\" and \"canary_weight\" in cfg:\n        if random.random() * 100 < cfg[\"canary_weight\"]:\n            version = cfg[\"version\"]\n            sha = cfg[\"sha256\"]\n            slot = \"canary\"\n        else:\n            # Fall back to production version\n            prod_cfg = _configs[\"production\"][\"prompts\"][prompt_key]\n            version = prod_cfg[\"version\"]\n            sha = prod_cfg[\"sha256\"]\n            slot = \"production\"\n    else:\n        version = cfg[\"version\"]\n        sha = cfg[\"sha256\"]\n        slot = env\n\n    prompt = load_prompt(cfg[\"name\"], version, sha)\n    return prompt, f\"{cfg['name']}@{version}[{slot}]\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every response records which version slot was used. This creates a natural A/B split in your observability data for the 24-hour soak period."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Automated Canary Rollback"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A background monitor checks canary error rates every 5 minutes during the soak window. If the error rate exceeds the gate threshold, it automatically reverts the canary config to the production version:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scripts/canary_monitor.py\nimport time, yaml, subprocess\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom prometheus_client import start_http_server\nimport requests\n\nPROMETHEUS_URL = \"http://prometheus:9090\"\nSOAK_HOURS = 24\nCHECK_INTERVAL_SECS = 300\nERROR_RATE_THRESHOLD = 0.01    # 1%\n\ndef get_error_rate(version: str, window: str = \"5m\") -> float:\n    query = (\n        f'sum(rate(prompt_errors_total{{version=\"{version}\"}}[{window}])) / '\n        f'sum(rate(prompt_requests_total{{version=\"{version}\"}}[{window}]))'\n    )\n    resp = requests.get(f\"{PROMETHEUS_URL}/api/v1/query\", params={\"query\": query})\n    result = resp.json()[\"data\"][\"result\"]\n    if not result: return 0.0\n    return float(result[0][\"value\"][1])\n\ndef rollback_canary(prompt_key: str):\n    prod_cfg = yaml.safe_load(Path(\"deploy/config/production.yaml\").read_text())\n    canary_cfg = yaml.safe_load(Path(\"deploy/config/canary.yaml\").read_text())\n    # Reset canary to match production for this prompt\n    canary_cfg[\"prompts\"][prompt_key] = prod_cfg[\"prompts\"][prompt_key]\n    Path(\"deploy/config/canary.yaml\").write_text(yaml.dump(canary_cfg))\n    subprocess.run([\"git\", \"add\", \"deploy/config/canary.yaml\"], check=True)\n    subprocess.run([\"git\", \"commit\", \"-m\",\n                    f\"rollback: canary {prompt_key} reverted (error rate exceeded)\"],\n                   check=True)\n    subprocess.run([\"git\", \"push\", \"origin\", \"main\"], check=True)\n    print(f\"ROLLBACK: {prompt_key} canary reverted to production version\")\n\ndef monitor_canary(prompt_key: str, canary_version: str):\n    deadline = time.time() + SOAK_HOURS * 3600\n    print(f\"Monitoring canary {prompt_key}@{canary_version} for {SOAK_HOURS}h...\")\n    while time.time() < deadline:\n        rate = get_error_rate(canary_version)\n        print(f\"Error rate: {rate:.4f} (threshold: {ERROR_RATE_THRESHOLD})\")\n        if rate > ERROR_RATE_THRESHOLD:\n            rollback_canary(prompt_key)\n            return False\n        time.sleep(CHECK_INTERVAL_SECS)\n    print(f\"Soak complete. Canary {canary_version} ready for production promotion.\")\n    return True\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    import sys\n    success = monitor_canary(sys.argv[1], sys.argv[2])\n    raise SystemExit(0 if success else 1)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Promoting from Canary to Production"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After the 24-hour soak with no gate violations, the promotion script updates the production config and opens a PR:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/bin/bash\n# scripts/graduate_canary.sh\nset -euo pipefail\n\nPROMPT_KEY=\"$1\"    # e.g. triage\nCANARY_CFG=\"deploy/config/canary.yaml\"\nPROD_CFG=\"deploy/config/production.yaml\"\n\n# Extract canary version and sha256 for this prompt\nCANARY_VERSION=$(python3 -c \"\nimport yaml; c=yaml.safe_load(open('$CANARY_CFG')); p=c['prompts']['$PROMPT_KEY']\nprint(p['version'])\n\")\nCANARY_SHA=$(python3 -c \"\nimport yaml; c=yaml.safe_load(open('$CANARY_CFG')); p=c['prompts']['$PROMPT_KEY']\nprint(p['sha256'])\n\")\n\necho \"Graduating $PROMPT_KEY@$CANARY_VERSION to production\"\n\n# Update production config\npython3 - <<PYEOF\nimport yaml\nprod = yaml.safe_load(open(\"$PROD_CFG\"))\nprod[\"prompts\"][\"$PROMPT_KEY\"][\"version\"] = \"$CANARY_VERSION\"\nprod[\"prompts\"][\"$PROMPT_KEY\"][\"sha256\"] = \"$CANARY_SHA\"\nopen(\"$PROD_CFG\", \"w\").write(yaml.dump(prod))\nPYEOF\n\ngit add \"$PROD_CFG\"\ngit commit -m \"promote($PROMPT_KEY): $CANARY_VERSION to production (canary soak passed)\"\ngit push origin main\n\necho \"Production config updated. CD pipeline will deploy $CANARY_VERSION.\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Observability: Tracking Version Distribution"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "During canary and immediately after production promotion, a version distribution dashboard shows which version is serving each request. The key metric is the split ratio between canary and production slots:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# src/metrics.py \u2014 instrument every Claude API call\nfrom prometheus_client import Counter, Histogram\n\nprompt_requests = Counter(\n    \"prompt_requests_total\",\n    \"Total prompt API calls\",\n    [\"prompt_name\", \"version\", \"slot\", \"env\"],\n)\nprompt_errors = Counter(\n    \"prompt_errors_total\",\n    \"Failed prompt API calls\",\n    [\"prompt_name\", \"version\", \"slot\", \"env\"],\n)\nprompt_latency = Histogram(\n    \"prompt_latency_seconds\",\n    \"End-to-end latency per prompt call\",\n    [\"prompt_name\", \"version\", \"slot\"],\n    buckets=[0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 5.0],\n)\n\ndef record_call(prompt_name, version, slot, env, duration_s, error=False):\n    labels = {\"prompt_name\": prompt_name, \"version\": version,\n              \"slot\": slot, \"env\": env}\n    prompt_requests.labels(**labels).inc()\n    prompt_latency.labels(\n        prompt_name=prompt_name, version=version, slot=slot\n    ).observe(duration_s)\n    if error:\n        prompt_errors.labels(**labels).inc()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
